9398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been training abroad for a long time in preparation for the Paris Games on funding from the government.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Soufiane El Bakkali of Morocco defended his title, clocking his season's best of 8:06.05 while Kenneth Rooks (8:06.41) of USA and Abraham Kibiwot (8:06.47) of Kenya took silver and bronze respectively.\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane El Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.8187050770339541, \"rank\": 0.22143874279380676, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 657, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9897307306044947, \"rank\": 0.0101344414028928, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9993835994454465, \"rank\": 0.0003477804655902993, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World record holder Lamecha Girma of Ethiopia did not finish the race as he fell on the track towards the end.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 848, \"entities\"